title: Why WeWork May Be the Next Casualty of the 2019 IPO Meltdown
text: The unicorn wants to be a diversified tech company that transforms industries through community building, yet bears can't look past its $1.9B loss.

title: Why Economist Gary Shilling Says the U.S. Will Win the Trade War
text: As the top buyer of Chinese-made goods and the biggest economy on earth, the U.S. has the upper hand in the trade conflict, Shilling argues.

title: Malaysian police raid Deloitte office for 1MDB-related documents: sources
text: Malaysian police raided the Kuala Lumpur office of audit firm Deloitte on Thursday to search for documents and records related to a multibillion-dollar scandal at state fund 1MDB, two police sources told Reuters.

title: Housing Market Health? Look At These Five Indicators, Not Existing Home Sales
text: The proper measures show good housing market health

title: China says U.S. needs to correct wrong actions to continue trade talks
text: The United States needs to correct its wrong actions if it wants to continue negotiations with China to end a damaging tariff war, China's Commerce Ministry said on Thursday, adding that talks should be based on mutual respect.

title: Semiconductor startup CNEX Labs alleged Huawei’s deputy chairman conspired to steal its intellectual property
text: A San Jose-based semiconductor startup being sued by Huawei for stealing trade secrets has hit back in court documents, accusing the Chinese firm’s deputy chairman of conspiring to steal its intellectual property, reports the Wall Street Journal.

title: Shares of Huawei suppliers tumble amid ongoing turmoil
text: Shares of Chinese telecommunications heavyweight Huawei's suppliers took a hit on Thursday afternoon amid the ongoing fallout surrounding the Chinese telecommunications giant.
